modules.description: Provides functions to inspect and serialize OCaml values, including closures and objects, with cycle detection and size limits to prevent infinite loops or excessive output. Works with arbitrary OCaml types, including complex structures and recursive data. Used to generate readable representations of exceptions or internal state during debugging.

Provides functions to convert OCaml values into human-readable strings or output streams, with controls for recursion limits and lazy value inspection. Works with arbitrary OCaml types, including tuples, lists, arrays, and recursive structures, using a custom notation for shared references and depth-limited traversal. Outputs can be directed to strings, files, buffers, or formatting modules for debugging or inspection purposes.
